SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: TO FURTHER SUPPORT COLLEGE BASEBALL, TROPHIES ARE AWARDED EACH YEAR TO THE MVP OF THE COLLEGE WORLD SERIES. THE TROPHIES ARE ORDERED IN GROUPS OF 10 DUE TO THE ECONOMIES OF THE ARTIST.

THE CORPORATION ADOPTED THE PROVISIONS OF FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING STANDARDS BOARD CODIFICATION TOPIC 740-10 RELATED TO UNCERTAIN INCOME TAX POSITIONS. AS A RESULT OF THE CORPORATION BEING TAXED AS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT, MANAGEMENT BELIEVES THERE ARE NO UNCERTAIN INCOME TAX POSITIONS TAKEN WHICH WOULD REQUIRE THE CORPORATION TO REFLECT A LIABILITY FOR UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS ON THE ACCOMPANYING STATEMENTS OF FINANCIAL POSITION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION REQUIRES THAT GRANTEE ORGANIZATIONS PROVIDE PHOTOGRAPHS OF COMPLETED PROJECTS FOR WHICH FUNDS WERE GRANTED.

KOLEY JESSEN, P.C., LLO RECEIVED COMPENSATION FOR CERTAIN LEGAL SERVICES PROVIDED TO COLLEGE WORLD SERIES OF OMAHA, INC. IN THE NORMAL COURSE OF ITS ACTIVITIES. THESE SERVICES WERE PROVIDED AT A REDUCED RATE AND IN ADDITION TO THE IN-KIND LEGAL SERVICES KOLEY JESSEN, P.C., LLO DONATED TO THE COLLEGE WORLD SERIES OF OMAHA, INC. IN THE NORMAL COURSE OF ITS ACTIVITIES. DAVID GOESCHEL, GENERAL COUNSEL, AND ERIC OXLEY, BOARD MEMBER, ARE SHAREHOLDERS OF KOLEY JESSEN, P.C., LLC. THESE TRANSACTIONS WERE REVIEWED AND APPROVED AS REASONABLE IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE ORGANIZATION'S CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY.
